'''Weston James Earl McKennie''' (born August 28, 1998) is an American professional [[soccer]] <!--Do not change to "football". Wikipedia articles are written in the style of English most associated with the subject, and as McKennie is American, please use American English --> player who plays primarily as a [[midfielder]] for [[Serie A]] club{{English football updater|Aston Villa}} [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]].  A highly versatile player, he has been described as a "[[Swiss Army knife]]" and is routinely deployed in any [[Outfield#In association football|outfield]] position except [[center-back]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Top 50 players at 2022 World Cup, No. 41: Weston McKennie |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/top-50-players-at-2022-world-cup-weston-mckennie |access-date=2024-05-06 |website=FOX Sports |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-02-12 |title=Charting Weston McKennie's unlikely rise at Juventus |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/charting-weston-mckennie-unlikely-rise-072500255.html |access-date=2025-02-21 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=O'Keeffe |first=Greg |title=USMNT midfielder Weston McKennie has what he wants this January – no transfer talk |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6084217/2025/01/24/weston-mckennie-interview-juventus-usmnt/ |access-date=2025-02-21 |work=The New York Times |date=January 25, 2025 |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

A youth prospect from [[FC Dallas]], McKennie began his senior club career at [[Bundesliga]] side [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] after rising through the team's academy sector. In [[2017–18 FC Schalke 04 season|2017–18]], he established himself as a first team player and played three full seasons. In August 2020, McKennie joined Serie A champions Juventus on loan, winning the [[2020 Supercoppa Italiana]]. The move was made permanent in March 2021, which he later won the [[2020–21 Coppa Italia]] in the same season. In 2023 he was loaned to [[Premier League]] club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]], after which he returned to Juventus and won the [[2023–24 Coppa Italia]].<ref name=":4" />

McKennie has represented the United States internationally at both the youth and senior levels. He made his senior debut in 2017 and has finished runner-up in the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] and won the [[CONCACAF Nations League]] in [[2021 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2021]], [[2023 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2023]], and [[2024 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2024]], winning the best player award of the 2021 tournament. Individually, he won a [[U.S. Soccer Player of the Year#U.S. Soccer Players of the Year|U.S. Soccer Male Player of the Year]] award in 2020.

==Early life==
Although born at [[Fort Lewis (Washington)|Fort Lewis]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], McKennie considers [[Little Elm, Texas]], his home town.<ref name=espn-howler/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ussoccer.com/players/m/weston-mckennie|title=Weston McKennie|publisher=U.S. Soccer}}</ref> He lived in [[Kaiserslautern]], Germany, from age six to nine as his father, a [[United States Air Force]] officer, was stationed at nearby [[Ramstein Air Base]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Weston McKennie: 10 things you might not know about Schalke's US starlet|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/weston-mckennie-10-things-on-schalke-s-usa-starlet-pulisic-usmnt-463874.jsp|access-date=March 3, 2021|website=bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website|language=en|archive-date=September 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924093333/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/weston-mckennie-10-things-on-schalke-s-usa-starlet-pulisic-usmnt-463874.jsp|url-status=dead}}</ref> McKennie started playing soccer for the local club FC Phönix Otterbach in 2004, before moving back to the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/club/schalke-04/133/blog/post/3090864 |last=Uerfsfeld |first=Stephan |title=Schalke's Weston McKennie dreaming of following Christian Pulisic's path|date=April 4, 2017 |publisher=[[ESPN FC]] |access-date=May 30, 2020}}</ref> McKennie played for the youth system of [[Major League Soccer]] side [[FC Dallas]] for seven years from 2009 to 2016, before moving to [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Sidway|first=Scott|date=September 23, 2016|title=How FC Dallas became home to the best academy in the United States|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/09/23/how-fc-dallas-became-home-best-academy-united-states|access-date=August 19, 2020|website=MLS}}</ref> His transfer to Schalke was the main catalyst for FC Dallas to create their reserve team, [[North Texas SC]], which played in [[USL League One]].<ref name=":0"/> In February 2016, McKennie signed a [[National Letter of Intent]] to play for the [[Virginia Cavaliers men's soccer|University of Virginia]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Virginia Welcomes 10 Student-Athletes for 2016-17|url=http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-soccer/spec-rel/022516aad.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326141706/http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-soccer/spec-rel/022516aad.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=March 26, 2016|website=[[Virginia Cavaliers men's soccer]]|publisher=[[University of Virginia]]|access-date=November 11, 2017|date=February 26, 2016}}</ref> but he subsequently turned down the scholarship offer to play for the Cavaliers, and instead sought to go professional.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Straus|first1=Brian|title=Schalke's Weston McKennie Copes With Missed World Cup, Eyes Bright US Future|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2017/11/10/weston-mckennie-schalke-usa-world-cup-2018-pulisic|magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|access-date=November 11, 2017|date=November 10, 2017}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Schalke 04===
====2016–2018====
[[File:Loco-Shal04 (9).jpg|thumb|McKennie with [[Schalke 04]] in 2018]]
In July 2016 McKennie declined to sign a [[Homegrown Player Rule (Major League Soccer)|Homegrown Player]] contract with [[FC Dallas]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stejskal|first1=Sam|title=Dallas trying to sign US U-20 Weston McKennie, say he hasn't joined Schalke|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/07/21/dallas-trying-sign-us-u-20-weston-mckennie-say-he-hasnt-joined-schalke|website=MLS|access-date=May 20, 2017}}</ref> He joined German [[Bundesliga]] side [[FC Schalke 04]] in August 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Joseph|first1=Brendan|title=Weston McKennie signs with FC Schalke|url=http://www.starsandstripesfc.com/2016/8/30/12710634/weston-mckennie-fc-schalke-american-usa|website=Stars and Stripes|date=August 30, 2016 |access-date=May 20, 2017}}</ref> After spending less than a year with Schalke's academy team, McKennie was promoted to the first-team squad in May 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/schalke-promote-american-duo-weston-mckennie-and-haji-wright-to-senior-squad-444638.jsp|title=Schalke promote American duo McKennie and Wright to senior squad|website=bundesliga.com|access-date=May 20, 2017|archive-date=March 29, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220329124221/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/schalke-promote-american-duo-weston-mckennie-and-haji-wright-to-senior-squad-444638.jsp|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his professional debut on May 20, 2017, as a 77th-minute substitute during a 1–1 draw with [[FC Ingolstadt 04]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/05/20/germany/bundesliga/fc-ingolstadt-04/fc-schalke-04/2255209/|title=Ingolstadt vs. Schalke 04–20 May 2017 – Soccerway|website=uk.soccerway.com}}</ref> This was his only appearance during the [[2016–17 FC Schalke 04 season|2016–17 season]].<ref name="2017–18 season">{{cite web |title=Weston McKennie |url=https://www.kicker.de/weston-mckennie/spieler/serie-a/2024-25/juventus-turin |website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |publisher=kicker |access-date=September 18, 2018 |language=de}}</ref> McKennie made his first start in September 2017 and signed a five-year contract shortly after.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/schalke-04/story/3214797/schalke-tie-us-youngster-weston-mckennie-to-new-five-year-deal|title=Schalke tie U.S. youngster Weston McKennie to new five-year deal|website=espnfc.com}}</ref> During the same year, McKennie made 21 appearances and scored 4 goals with Schalke's U-19 team.

During the 2017–18 season, McKennie cemented his place as a member of the Schalke first team at the age of 19. He made 22 appearances in the Bundesliga.<ref name="SW">{{Soccerway|459693|accessdate=May 26, 2021}}</ref> He finished the [[2017–18 FC Schalke 04 season|2017–18 season]] with 25 appearances in all competitions.<ref name="2017–18 season"/> Further, he proved to be a valuable asset to Schalke given his versatility, with McKennie playing multiple positions in the midfield and defense for the team.<ref>{{Cite web|title=What is Weston McKennie's best position for Schalke and the USA?|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/what-is-weston-mckennie-s-best-position-for-schalke-and-the-usa-usmnt-40|access-date=August 19, 2020|website=bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website|language=en}}</ref>

====2018–2020====
During the 2018–19 season, McKennie further increased his position with the Bundesliga club, starting 25 games for the club in both the [[Bundesliga]], [[DFB-Pokal]], and [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref name="SW"/> Overall, McKennie made 33 appearances for the club and scored 2 goals in all competitions,<ref name="SW"/> in which he scored his first Champions League goal in a 1–0 away win over [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/history/video/024c-0e68d695d124-d073d97d3257-1000--weston-mckennie-my-first-ucl-goal/ |title=Weston McKennie: My first #UCL goal |website=UEFA |date=December 6, 2018 }}</ref>

Under new manager [[David Wagner (soccer)|David Wagner]], McKennie further established himself as an important part and valuable asset of a team that struggled to deal with the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Weston McKennie shines for floundering Schalke 04|url=https://www.socceramerica.com/publications/article/85742/weston-mckennie-shines-for-floundering-schalke-04.html|access-date=August 19, 2020|website=www.socceramerica.com|date=May 28, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> McKennie made a total of 28 appearances and scored three goals for Schalke in the Bundesliga.<ref name="SW"/> McKennie made a further four appearances in the DFB-Pokal for the club.<ref name="SW"/> On May 30, 2020, during a 1–0 loss to [[SV Werder Bremen]], McKennie wore an armband that said “Justice for George” following the [[murder of George Floyd]] in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tampabay.com/sports/rowdies/2020/05/30/american-weston-mckennie-wears-justice-for-george-armband-during-bundesliga-game/|title=American Weston McKennie wears 'Justice for George' armband during Bundesliga game|publisher=tampabay.com|date=May 30, 2020}}</ref>

=== Juventus ===
[[File:Weston McKennie vs Zenit 2021-10-20 (cropped).jpg|thumb|McKennie playing for Juventus in October 2021]]

==== 2020–2022 ====
On August 29, 2020, it was announced that McKennie joined [[Serie A]] side [[Juventus]] on a year-long loan.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|last=Juventus.com|title=Welcome Weston!|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/welcome-weston|access-date=August 29, 2020|website=Juventus.com|language=en}}</ref> In doing so, he became Juventus' first player—and Serie A's fifth—from the [[United States]].<ref name=":3"/> The move was structured as an initial year-long loan for a fee of €4.5 million, with an option to make the loan permanent at the end of the season.<ref name=":3"/> However, if McKennie met certain performance incentives, the option would automatically trigger, and the deal would become permanent.<ref name=":3"/> In both scenarios, the deal would be for €18.5 million, which could rise an additional €7 million.<ref name=":3"/> On September 7, McKennie had his introductory press conference and was given the number 14.<ref>{{Cite web | agency=Associated Press|title=McKennie: Juventus Move 'A Dream That Has Become a Reality'|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2020/09/07/weston-mckennie-juventus-introduction-ronaldo-pirlo|access-date=September 8, 2020|magazine=Sports Illustrated|date=September 7, 2020 |language=en-us}}</ref>

McKennie made his league debut for Juventus on September 20, starting and playing the full 90 minutes in a 3–0 league home win against [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Juventus-Sampdoria, le pagelle: McKennie stupisce, Kulusevski geniale {{!}} Goal.com|url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/juventus-sampdoria-pagelle/15dzjf8v3avbr1loue0aso6qp7|access-date=September 20, 2020|website=www.goal.com}}</ref> McKennie made his [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut for the club in the second match of the group stage, coming on in the 75th minute of a 2–0 home defeat to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Juventus vs. Barcelona score: Dembele, Messi fire Koeman's men past Ronaldo-less Juve|url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/juventus-vs-barcelona-score-dembele-messi-fire-koemans-men-past-ronaldo-less-juve/live/|access-date=October 29, 2020|website=CBSSports.com|date=October 29, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On November 1, McKennie got on the score sheet for the first time for Juventus, earning an assist on the opening goal by [[Álvaro Morata]] in a 4–1 win against [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Spezia vs. Juventus - Football Match Report - November 1, 2020 - ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=583105|access-date=November 1, 2020|website=ESPN.com|language=en}}</ref> On November 24, McKennie started a Champions League match against [[Ferencvárosi TC|Ferencváros]], becoming the first American international in Italy to do so.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2029434--juventus-vs-ferencvaros/ |title=Juventus 2–1 Ferencváros |website=UEFA |date=November 24, 2020 }}</ref> McKennie scored his first goal for Juventus on December 5, in the ''[[Derby della Mole]]'' against [[Torino F.C.|Torino]]; he scored the equalizer of the match, which eventually ended in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{Cite web|date=December 5, 2020|title=USMNT's McKennie leads Juventus comeback in Derby della Mole (video)|url=https://soccer.nbcsports.com/2020/12/05/usmnts-mckennie-leads-juventus-comeback-in-derby-della-mole-video/|access-date=December 5, 2020|website=ProSoccerTalk {{!}} NBC Sports|language=en-US}}</ref> Three days later, McKennie scored his first Champions League goal for Juventus—a [[Bicycle kick|scissor kick]] on the volley—against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]],<ref>{{Cite web|last=Randhawa|first=Jaikuran|date=December 8, 2020|title=Video: McKennie scores scissor kick for Juventus vs Barcelona|url=https://www.caughtoffside.com/2020/12/08/video-weston-mckennie-scores-amazing-scissor-kick-for-juventus-vs-barcelona/|access-date=December 8, 2020|website=CaughtOffside|language=en}}</ref> helping his team win 3–0 away from home and finish in first place in their group.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Barcelona vs. Juventus - Football Match Summary - December 8, 2020 - ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=585770|access-date=December 8, 2020|website=ESPN.com|language=en}}</ref> On January 6, 2021, McKennie scored a goal against league-leaders [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] in a 3–1 away win; it was Milan's first league defeat in 27 games.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=January 6, 2021|title=Chiesa show, la Juve si rilancia: Milan ko 3–1|url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/2021/01/06/milan-juventus-risultato-gol|access-date=January 6, 2021|website=sport.sky.it|language=it}}</ref>

On March 3, 2021, Juventus exercised their purchase option for €18.5 million, plus €6.5 million in potential bonuses, on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|date=March 3, 2021|title=Ufficiale il riscatto di Weston McKennie|url=https://www.juventus.com/it/news/articoli/ufficiale-il-riscatto-di-weston-mckennie|access-date=March 3, 2021|website=[[Juventus FC|Juventus]]|language=it}}</ref> McKennie started for Juventus in the [[2021 Coppa Italia Final|Coppa Italia Final]] against [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]]; he assisted [[Dejan Kulusevski]] for the team's first goal in an eventual 2–1 win.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|title=Atalanta vs. Juventus - Football Match Summary - May 19, 2021 - ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/594857|access-date=May 19, 2021|website=ESPN.com|language=en}}</ref> McKennie finished the [[2020–21 Juventus FC season|2020–21 season]] with six goals in 46 appearances in all competitions.<ref name="SW"/> McKennie scored his first goal of the season in a 2–1 loss to [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on October 27, and followed it up with a second goal in another 2–1 loss to [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]] three days later.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Juventus fall to injury-time defeat|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/59070230|access-date=November 3, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Juventus drop to ninth after fourth loss|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/59105680|access-date=November 3, 2021}}</ref> On January 12, 2022, McKennie scored the opener in the [[2021 Supercoppa Italiana]] match, which the team eventually lost 2–1 against [[Inter Milan]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Juventus.com |title=Sanchez all'ultimo respiro, la Supercoppa va all'Inter - Juventus |url=https://www.juventus.com/it/news/articoli/sanchez-all-ultimo-respiro-la-supercoppa-va-all-inter |access-date=March 23, 2022 |website=Juventus.com |language=it}}</ref> On February 22, in a Champions League game against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]], McKennie injured his metatarsal following a foul by [[Pervis Estupiñán]], forcing him to prematurely end his season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=March 6, 2022 |title=Serie A, Tegola Juventus - Allegri conferma: "Stagione finita per McKennie" |url=https://www.eurosport.it/calcio/serie-a/2021-2022/serie-a-tegola-juventus-allegri-conferma-stagione-finita-per-mckennie_sto8831646/story.shtml |access-date=March 23, 2022 |website=Eurosport |language=it}}</ref>

====Loan to Leeds United====
On January 30, 2023, McKennie joined English side [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] on loan for the remainder of the [[2022–23 Leeds United F.C. season|2022–23 season]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64460874 McKennie Leeds loan]</ref> He made his Leeds debut on February 5, 2023, as a second-half substitute in the Premier League 1–0 defeat to [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64442954?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=KARANGA mcKennie Leeds debut]</ref> He made 20 appearances for the team across all competitions, including 16 starts in the Premier League, but failed to score any goals before Leeds were ultimately relegated on the last day of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Leeds FC Player Appearances {{!}} Past & Present {{!}} Soccer Base |url=https://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=1524&teamTabs=stats&season_id=155 |access-date=2023-06-08 |website=www.soccerbase.com}}</ref>

==== 2023–present ====
After his Leeds loan, McKennie returned to the Juventus first team for the [[2023–24 Juventus FC season|2023–24 season]] and took the number 16.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Juventus.com |title=Weston McKennie {{!}} Midfielder Juventus Men's First Team |url=https://www.juventus.com/en/teams/first-team-men/squad/weston-mckennie |access-date=2024-05-09 |website=Juventus.com |language=en}}</ref> On September 16, 2023, he made his 100th appearance for Juventus, creating a long ball assist in the 3–1 victory over [[SS Lazio|Lazio]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-16 |title=USMNT star Weston McKennie marks 100th Juventus appearance with superb assist but Tim Weah misses golden chance to grab first Serie A goal in win over Lazio {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/weston-mckennie-tim-weah-juventus-lazio-usmnt/bltd85c555faa437e4a |access-date=2023-09-27 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> Reestablished as a starter in the Juventus midfield, on December 23 he created an assist in the 2–1 win over [[Frosinone Calcio|Frosinone]]. On January 11, 2024, McKennie created two assists in the 4–0 victory over Frosinone in the [[2023–24 Coppa Italia]] quarter-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-11 |title=Weston McKennie, the maestro! USMNT star provides two spectacular assists to lead Juventus to Coppa Italia rout of Frosinone {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/usmnt-weston-mckennie-juventus-coppa-italia/blt7b12e5bb5117eda1 |access-date=2024-05-06 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On January 21 he recorded a league assist in the 3–0 victory over [[US Lecce|Lecce]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Juventus 3-0 Lecce (Jan 21, 2024) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/679427 |access-date=2024-05-09 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On February 25, he repeated the same feat against Frosinone by creating two assists in league play.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-25 |title=WATCH: USMNT's Weston McKennie delivers two clutch assists to Dusan Vlahovic in key Juventus win |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/watch-usmnts-weston-mckennie-delivers-two-clutch-assists-to-dusan-vlahovic-in-key-juventus-win/ |access-date=2024-05-06 |website=CBSSports.com |language=en}}</ref>  On March 10, he created two league assists in the 2–2 draw to [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-10 |title=Weston McKennie is back with a bang! USMNT star provides two brilliant assists on return from injury - but sloppy Juventus settle for draw with Atalanta {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/weston-mckennie-back-with-bang-usmnt-star-two-brilliant-assists-return-injury-but-sloppy-juventus-draw-atalanta/blt280a2170cbb479cf |access-date=2024-05-09 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On April 2, 2024, he recorded his season-record 10th assist (7th season league assist) against [[SS Lazio|Lazio]] in the [[2023–24 Coppa Italia]] semi-finals, helping them to the cup final.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-02 |title=Weston McKennie's 10th assist of season keeps Juventus on track for silverware as Bianconeri thump Lazio in leg one of Coppa Italia semifinals {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/weston-mckennie-juventus-lazio-usmnt-coppa-italia/blt32906df524927c18 |access-date=2024-04-05 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> McKennie started in the [[2024 Coppa Italia final]] and played the full 90 minutes, where Juventus won 1–0 and he secured his second Coppa Italia trophy.<ref name=":1" />

On August 22, 2024, McKennie extended his contract with Juventus until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Says |first=Bianconero |date=2024-08-22 |title=McKennie agrees new Juventus contract until 2026 |url=https://football-italia.net/mckennie-agrees-new-juventus-contract-2026/ |access-date=2024-08-22 |website=football-italia.net |language=en-GB}}</ref> On September 17, he scored in the club's opening [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] game, a 3–1 win over [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Juventus 3-1 PSV (17 Sep, 2024) Game Analysis |url=https://africa.espn.com/football/report/_/gameId/720418 |access-date=2024-09-17 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On October 27, he recorded two assists in the 4–4 draw with [[Inter Milan]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-27 |title=Weston McKennie records two assists, Tim Weah scores as USMNT duo play roles in eight-goal thriller as Juventus and Inter share point in Derby d'Italia {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/weston-mckennie-tim-weah-usmnt-juventus-inter-milan-serie-a/blt74bcd9a3648f87da |access-date=2024-10-27 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> In the following game on October 30, he scored in the 2–2 draw against [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Juventus 2-2 Parma (Oct 30, 2024) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/712208 |access-date=2024-10-31 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On December 11, he scored a volley goal in the 2–0 win over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the Champions League group stage.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-11 |title=Weston McKennie scores stunning side volley for Juventus vs Man City off Weah assist (video) |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/soccer/news/weston-mckennie-scores-stunning-side-volley-for-juventus-vs-man-city-off-weah-assist-video |access-date=2024-12-11 |website=NBC Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> On February 11 in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Bracket|Champions League knockout phase]], he scored against PSV again winning 2–1.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-02-11 |title=WATCH: USMNT star Weston McKennie scores Champions League screamer in Juventus' win over PSV {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/watch-usmnt-star-weston-mckennie-scores-champions-league-screamer-in-juventus-clash-with-psv/blte6bb0f612a7ebcc6 |access-date=2025-05-04 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

For the [[2025–26 Juventus FC season|2025–26 season]], McKennie again changed his number to 22 in respect to his teammate [[Michele Di Gregorio]] whose late father was fond of his previous 16 number.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Vertelney |first=Seth |title=McKennie called 'best teammate ever' for Di Gregorio gesture |url=https://prosoccerwire.usatoday.com/story/sports/usmnt/2025/08/23/mckennie-called-best-teammate-ever-di-gregorio-gesture/85788686007/ |access-date=2026-02-18 |website=Pro Soccer Wire |language=en-US}}</ref> January 22, 2026 marked him scoring in three consecutive Champions League games in a row after the 2–0 win over [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=read |first=Ryan Tolmich·2 min |date=2026-01-21 |title=WATCH: USMNT star Weston McKennie scores in third consecutive Champions League game to lead Juventus to win over Benfica |url=https://uk.sports.yahoo.com/news/watch-usmnt-star-weston-mckennie-202632459.html |access-date=2026-01-23 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=The official website for European football |url=https://www.uefa.com/errors/ |access-date=2026-01-23 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> He was named the Juventus Player of the Month for January with 3 goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-02-05 |title=USMNT's Weston McKennie is Juventus' Player of the Month for January after scoring three goals in seven appearances {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/usmnt-s-weston-mckennie-is-juventus-player-of-the-month-for-january-after-scoring-three-goals-in-seven-appearances/bltbaabf0552951c194 |access-date=2026-02-18 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On February 6, he scored against [[SS Lazio|Lazio]], marking his best goalscoring season to date with 7 goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-02-09 |title=Road to World Cup 2026: McKennie Hits Standout Mark Amid Stellar Form |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/road-to-world-cup-2026-mckennie-hits-standout-mark-2-9-26 |access-date=2026-02-18 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref>  On February 14, he created 2 assists in the 2–3 loss to rivals [[Inter Milan|Inter]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-02-15 |title=Americans Abroad: Weston McKennie shines in controversial Juventus loss as Patrick Agyemang reaches scoring milestone {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/americans-abroad-weston-mckennie-juventus-patrick-agyemang-derby-brenden-aaronson-sergino-dest/blt05fbfe46e51dae5b |access-date=2026-02-15 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On February 25, McKennie scored a late aggregate equalizer in the second leg win against [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] to break his best ever Champions League season with 4 goals, though Juventus would ultimately be eliminated by aggregate in overtime.<ref>{{Cite news |last=O'Keeffe |first=Greg |date=2026-02-25 |title=Weston McKennie's heroics force extra time, but Juventus crashes out of Champions League |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7071223/2026/02/25/weston-mckennie-goal-juventus-galatasaray-champions-league-usmnt/ |access-date=2026-02-26 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> His goal also made him only one goal away (11) from the American all-time Champions League goalscoring leader [[Christian Pulisic]] (12)<ref>{{Cite web |title=Most Champions League Goals By An American |url=https://www.statmuse.com/fc/ask/most-champions-league-goals-by-an-american |access-date=2026-05-29 |website=StatMuse |language=en}}</ref>, and only the third Juventus midfielder to score 10+ career Champions League goals, with [[Pavel Nedvěd]] (11) and [[Michel Platini]] (17).<ref>{{Cite web |title=IFFHS |url=https://iffhs.com/posts/4958 |access-date=2026-02-26 |website=iffhs.com}}</ref> On March 2, 2026, McKennie agreed to a new contract with Juventus that will keep him at the club until 2030.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Horncastle |first=James |last2=Tenorio |first2=Paul |date=2026-03-02 |title=USMNT midfielder Weston McKennie agrees Juventus contract extension until 2030 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6884631/2026/03/02/weston-mckennie-juventus-contract-extension/ |access-date=2026-03-02 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> He ended his highest goalscoring season with 9 goals and 8 assists across all competitions. For his performances, McKennie was named on the [[2025–26 Serie A#Awards|2025–26 Serie A Team of the Season]].<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |last=Arts |first=Electronic |date=2026-04-17 |title=Serie A Team of the Season (TOTS) - EA SPORTS FC™ Football Ultimate Team - EA SPORTS Official Site |url=https://www.ea.com/games/ea-sports-fc/fc-26/tots/serie-a |access-date=2026-04-16 |website=Electronic Arts Inc. |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Weston McKennie WC2022.jpg|thumb|left|200px|McKennie with the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].]]

McKennie has played with various United States youth teams, including the under-17 and under-20 national teams. McKennie earned his first senior team callup for the United States' friendly against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] on November 14, 2017, scoring on his debut.<ref>{{cite news|title=USA's new era starts with draw against European champions Portugal|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/nov/14/usa-portugal-score-friendly-weston-mckennie|newspaper=The Guardian|date=November 14, 2017 |access-date=November 16, 2017|last1=Dart |first1=Tom }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Weston McKennie man of the match as U.S. earn draw in Portugal|url=http://www.espnfc.com/team/united-states/660/blog/post/3270939/us-draw-portugal-as-weston-mckennie-man-of-the-match|website=espnfc.com|access-date=November 16, 2017}}</ref> McKennie's first international assist came in the opening game of the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] against [[Guyana national football team|Guyana]] at [[Allianz Field]] in a 4–0 win. McKennie scored the lone goal for the U.S. on June 30, 2019, to help them secure a 1–0 win in the Gold Cup quarter-finals against [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]]. McKennie notched his second goal in the semi-finals against [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]] in the 19th minute.

On October 12, 2019, McKennie scored the fastest hat-trick in the U.S. men's national team's history, scoring three goals in thirteen minutes in a [[2019–20 CONCACAF Nations League qualifying|CONCACAF Nations League]] game against [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/oct/11/usa-cuba-nations-league-weston-mckennie|title=Weston McKennie scores record hat-trick as USA hammer seven past Cuba|last1=sport|first1=Guardian|date=October 12, 2019|work=The Guardian|access-date=October 12, 2019|last2=agencies|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On June 6, 2021, McKennie scored a decisive 2–2 equalizer in the [[2021 CONCACAF Nations League Final]] against rivals [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]], bringing the game to [[Overtime (association football)|extra time]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Das|first1=Andrew|date=June 7, 2021|title=U.S. 3, Mexico 2: All the Plot Twists|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/06/07/sports/soccer/usa-mexico-nations-league-final.html?action=click&module=Features&pgtype=Homepage}}</ref> The game ultimately ended 3–2 to the United States, and McKennie was nominated Player of the Tournament.<ref>{{cite tweet|author=CONCACAF|author-link=CONCACAF|user=CNationsLeague|number=1401770588742598660|date=June 6, 2021|title=Weston McKennie of the United States has won the Scotiabank FC Best Player Award of the Concacaf Nations League.|access-date=June 7, 2021}}</ref> On September 7, 2021, during the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF third round|final round]] of [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifying]], McKennie was dropped from the national team for breaking [[COVID-19 pandemic|COVID-19]] team protocols by bringing a guest into his hotel room while the team was in [[Nashville, Tennessee]], for their match against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]]. As a result, he missed the final two matches of the series.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Carlisle |first1=Jeff |title=McKennie dismissed by USMNT for two COVID protocol violations, including bringing unauthorized individual into bubble - sources |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/united-states-usa/story/4470334|website=ESPN |access-date=November 28, 2022 |date=September 7, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Christian Pulisic, USMNT eye 'results' after Weston McKennie exit |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/united-states-usa/story/4470707 |website=ESPN.com |access-date=November 28, 2022 |date=September 8, 2021}}</ref>

[[File:USMNT vs. Trinidad and Tobago (48125032298) (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|200px|McKennie playing for [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] against [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] in 2023.]]

McKennie won the [[2023 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2023 CONCACAF Nations League]] against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] and the [[2024 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2024 CONCACAF Nations League]] against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]], where he assisted [[Tyler Adams]] for the opening goal in [[2024 CONCACAF Nations League final|the final]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-25 |title='Absolutely sensational': Adams' long-distance goal gives USMNT lead over Mexico |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/39803911/usmnt-tyler-adams-goal-concacaf-nations-league-final-mexico |access-date=2024-05-06 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> In June 2024, McKennie along with US teammates [[Folarin Balogun]], [[Chris Richards (soccer)|Chris Richards]] and [[Timothy Weah]] all suffered [[Racism in association football|racist abuse]] after the national team lost in the [[2024 Copa América]] to Panama.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c844jrxewv8t|title=Copa America: USA 1-2 Panama - Timothy Weah suffers racist abuse after red card|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
McKennie is known for his versatility as a player. During his time at Schalke, McKennie played in numerous positions including in midfield, as a center-back, full-back, and even as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=What is Weston McKennie's best position for Schalke and the USA?|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/what-is-weston-mckennie-s-best-position-for-schalke-and-the-usa-usmnt-40|access-date=August 29, 2020|website=bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website|language=en}}</ref> In addition, he is an often-utilized proponent of the long throw-in, deploying an unorthodox sideways wind-up technique prior to launching.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://the18.com/es/soccer-news/weston-mckennie-long-throw-stuns-leeds-fans?amp|title=Today Leeds fans learned that Weston McKennie can throw a ball over them mountains|last=Moore|first=David|website=The18.com|date=6 May 2023|access-date=13 January 2024}}</ref> However, he has primarily played as either a box-to-box midfielder or in a deeper-lying defensive role.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|date=January 10, 2019|title=Tactical Analysis: Weston McKennie, Schalke's jack-of-all-trades|url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/player-analysis/weston-mckennie-schalke-tactical-analysis-statistics|access-date=August 29, 2020|website=Total Football Analysis Magazine|language=en-GB}}</ref> During his time with Juventus, he has been used in several midfield positions, including as a [[Midfielder#Wide midfielder|wide midfielder]], in a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|holding role]], or even as a more [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|offensive-minded]] [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]], known as the ''[[Midfielder#Mezzala|mezzala]]'' role in Italian soccer jargon.<ref name="maghetto">{{cite news |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/sport/calcio/juve_mckennie_e_un_maghetto_per_pirlo-5743523.html |title=La Juve e McKennie, c'è un maghetto per Pirlo |trans-title=Juve and McKennie, there's a little wizard for Pirlo |work=Il Messaggero |language=it |last1=Mauro |first1=Alberto |date=February 4, 2021 |access-date=May 20, 2021 }}</ref>

McKennie's primary attributes are his defensive skills and work rate, as well as his ability to win back the ball.<ref name=":2"/> Furthermore, his passing allows him to dictate the flow of the game and push the ball forward from [[Midfielder#Deep-lying playmaker (Strolling 10)|deep-lying positions in midfield]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=November 6, 2017|title=Scout Report: Weston McKennie {{!}} Schalke's American stalwart|url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2017/11/07/scout-report-weston-mckennie-schalkes-american-stalwart/|access-date=August 29, 2020|website=Outside of the Boot|language=en-US}}{{Dead link|date=August 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> His ball-winning qualities, combined with his positioning, tactical intelligence, eye for goal from midfield, and ability to make late attacking runs into the box led Alberto Mauro of ''[[Il Messaggero]]'' to compare him to former Juventus midfielders [[Edgar Davids]] and [[Arturo Vidal]]; McKennie's technical ability was cited as an area in need of improvement, however.<ref name="maghetto"/>

== Personal life ==
McKennie has been a fan of the [[Wizarding World]] since first reading a [[Harry Potter]] book at the age of 6.<ref name="McKennieHP1">{{Cite web |title=Weston McKennie has his dream Harry Potter video game endorsement |url=https://prosoccerwire.usatoday.com/story/sports/mls/2023/02/10/weston-mckennie-harry-potter-goal-celebration-hogwarts-legacy/77432258007/ |date=February 10, 2023 |first=Seth |last=Vertelney |access-date=May 10, 2026 |website=[[USA Today]]}}</ref> He has a Harry Potter lightning bolt tattoo,<ref name="McKennieHP2">{{Cite web |title=Weston McKennie, Tim Weah link up for historic, all-American goal vs. Man City |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/weston-mckennie-tim-weah-link-up-historic-all-american-goal-vs-man-city |date=December 11, 2024 |website=[[Fox Sports (United States)|Fox Sports]] |accessdate=May 10, 2026}}</ref> and his signature goal celebration involves waving his hand as if using a wand to cast a spell.<ref name="McKennieHP1" /><ref name="McKennieHP2" /><ref>{{cite web |title=Weston McKennie became the top American goalscorer in Italian soccer history, then celebrated by pretending to be Harry Potter |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/weston-mckennie-juventus-breaks-serie-a-record-celebration-harry-potter-2021-2 |first=Barnaby |last=Lane |date=February 23, 2021 |website=[[Business Insider]] |accessdate=May 10, 2026}}</ref>

